postdoctoral researchers.  In the 2012-13 academic year, female students made up 34% of undergraduates and 40% of postgraduates, although in some areas of study, suc</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">h as postgraduate medicine, women accounted for over half</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">women make up </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">nearly 40% of staff</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> on research grades</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> but this relatively encouraging representation is not sustained</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18.15pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18.15pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">Perceived Barriers for Women in STEM Academic Careers and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">Examples of Good</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps"> Practice</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18.15pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18.15pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18.15pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman