ont-size:11pt">n its response to</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> the Sc</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ience and Technology Committee</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> the College hopes to assist the inquiry by providing </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> brief</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> overview of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">its experience</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> as well as </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">examples of good practice and measures it ha</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> taken to enhance the career progression of its female academic community. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18.15pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">Fixed Term Contracts</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.25pt; padding-left:4.9pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Progression to an academic STEM career </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">usually </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">requires staff to m</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ove through a number of ‘post-doctoral’ positions. These positions are gra</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">nt funded and tend </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">to be fixed-term</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, or if the contract is not fixed-term, the funds to support the position are</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. Such contracts </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">are relatively unstable in what is known to be a cruc</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ial</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> period in an academic career for both men and women. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">From results of focus groups/discussions/surveys</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">fixed-term</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> contracts are </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">considered by women</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> to be a particular barrier in relation to their careers and planning</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The fact that the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">y</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> are </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">normally </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">h</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">eld </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">relatively </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">early on in an academic career also increases the likelihood that </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">a woman will hold such a contract</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">around the same time </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">as </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">she </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">may</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">be starting a family. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> V</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ariations in rules </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">also </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">mean that grant</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s are not always able to be suspended </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">when a r</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">esearcher tak</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">es a period of maternity leave.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18.15pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">Creating an Inclusive Culture</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="8" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.25pt; padding-left:4.9pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The College established its Academic Opportunities Committee in 1999 to help address the under-representation of female academic staff, and part of its important work has been to highlight and change aspects of university culture that can hinder female car</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">eer progression.   In recent years, it has been </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">seen as </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">essential for the committee to have senior male membership</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and activity has been directed by the belief that ‘what benefits women benefits men too’</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="9" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.25pt; padding-left:4.9pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">With a relatively small number of female staff rea</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">ching the top of the academic ladder, consequently there are a small number of female role models that can provide inspiration and/or guidance and mentoring to those earlier on in their careers. In particular, there may be a shortage of highly visible seni</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">or women who have children</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt"> or other caring responsibilities</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="10" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; letter-spacing:-0.15pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18.15pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Specialised academic staff development is provided for mid-career women</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> which has resulted in career progression for many participants</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. In particular, there is a residential Development Centre </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">for Female Academics, with specific activities aimed at overcoming barriers raised by the participants. Longer term support following the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">programme</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> is provided by ongoing meetings and one to one coaching.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">The College also offers and encourages formal and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">informal coaching and mentoring opportunities</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt"> together with a wide range of other development opportunities</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt"> taken up by female academics</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">.  In addition to assisting with developing individuals’ careers, the aim is to support women to achieve more senior po</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">sitions so that, in turn, the College is able to appoint to senior roles from within.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="11" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18.15pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">In recognition that postdoctoral research can be a difficult stepping stone to an academic career, the College has a well-</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">regarded</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> Post Doc Development Centre which spec</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ialises in support and development for early career researchers. The Centre provides tailored support and coaching for post docs, including mock interviews, CV assistance and networking opportunities. The Post Doc Development Centre also runs the internati</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">onally acclaimed Springboard development programme. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">  The College also established its </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">own successful </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Junior Research Fellowship </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">(JRF) </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Scheme</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">in 2009 </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">to</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> help facilitate the move from post doc to academic.  More than 70 fellows later, the JRF Scheme is once</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> again open for 2014 start dates</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="12" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; letter-spacing:-0.15pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18.15pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">The College endeavours to celebrate the achievements of female academic staff widely. An annual Athena Lecture is held in which a female academic</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">, who may be</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt"> internal or external to the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">College,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt"> is invited to speak about h</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">er career, life and achievements. This lecture has recently been replicated more locally in the College’s School of Public Health. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt"> A celebratory lunch is held annually for female academics who have been promoted.  Pictures and stories in publications and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">the website are selected carefully to portray positive images of female success and activity.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18.15pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="13" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18.15pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> College has created the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Julia Higgins Medal and Awards </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">which </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">are awarded annually to recognise individuals and departments that have made a significant </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">contribution to the support of academic women at the College</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span><a name="_ftnref2"></a><a href="#_ftn2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="14" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18.15pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Imperial College London has made a pledge to its staff and students that it shall take ‘</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">the necessary action to eliminate all forms of discrimination, especially direct and indirect forms of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">harassment, bullying and victimisation’</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, as working in a culture where such behaviour occurs is a barrier to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">both women and men’s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> careers, academic or otherwise. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="15" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18.15pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The College has </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">also </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">implemented </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Imperial Expectations</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, a set </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">of seven statements which arti</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">culate how the College expects its leaders, managers and supervisors to behave. These expectations require leaders and managers to behave and develop their staff appropriately</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and they s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">p</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ecifically require managers to e</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ncourage inclusive participation and</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> eliminate discrimination</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. The </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">E</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">xpectations</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> are intended to help the College attract and retain its talented staff, of which its female academics key. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18.15pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">Equality and Diversity in Recruitment and Promotion</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18.15pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="16" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18.15pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">An Academic Diversity Task Force </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">was </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">es</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">tablished </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">in 2</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">0</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">12 </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">was </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">asked </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">to</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> recommend actions to improve the diversity of academic staff at junior and middle levels as these are areas at which the ‘leaky pipeline’ has been identified to be at its most detrimental. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">  The T</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ask </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">F</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">orce</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">’s recommendations were co</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">nsidered and approved by the College’s Management Board and are being implemented during 2013/14.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">A couple of e</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">xamples </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">from a wide range </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">of actions are:</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> to ensure that academic positions are always advertised with </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">wide</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">st</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> possible</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> criteria</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> in order to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">at</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">tract a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">more diverse</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> pool of candidates</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> the College’s recruitment material is </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">inclusive and welcoming.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="17" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18.15pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The College operates a transparent and unbiased recruitment and promotions process which is based on merit, regardless of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">all the protected </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">characteristics,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> but </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">the College is aware that unconscious bias may </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">r</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">estrict the progression of female academic staff</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> The College has taken steps to raise awareness of the influence </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">unco</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">nscious bias in decision making</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">and a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">comprehensive </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">programme of</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> u</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">nconscious bias training </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">is underway</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18.15pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="18" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18.15pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">To ensure that the College’s academic promotions procedure is as clear and transparent as possible</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> briefings are run </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">annually </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> the College’s three largest campuses. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">T</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">wo sets of briefings are run, one focussing on ‘</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">the application</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> process</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">’ and the second on ‘the interview’.  </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18.15pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">Family and Childcare Responsibilities</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">              </span></p><ol start="19" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18.15pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">There is a lack of obvious part-time opportunities in academic STEM departments; this may present a barrier to women who do not wish to work full-time.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The College promotes flexible working but female academics feel the pressure to come back to work full-time in order to ensure that their careers are not put on hold.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="20" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18.15pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">A high degree of both national, and international, mobility can be required to progress </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">a scientific academic career. This may act as a barrier for staff with childcare</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, or other caring,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> responsibilities. Unsociable hours of work and the requirement to be ‘on call’ may be a particular barrier to the College’</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> female clinical academic staff.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="21" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18.15pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The College provides high quality in-house childcare by way of its Early Years Education Centre, which has been rated as Outstanding by Ofsted. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">It also provides a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> childcare support scheme by providing a £124 per month tax free sum to each parent of a child</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> under five.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="22" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18.15pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The College established the Elsie Widdowson Fellowship award in 2000</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. Then unique in UK Higher Education,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">purpose of the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> Fellowship Awards are</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> to allow female academics to concentrate fully on their research work upon returning from mater</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">nity / adoption leave. The award allows the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">academic’s department to relieve them </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">of any teaching or admin duties in order to concentrate fully on research.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The Award provides central funding for 50% of</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> the salary costs for 12 months.  For women without he</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">avy teaching commitments, the funding can be used for supporting research staff salary or consumables. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Applications for Elsie Widdowson Fellowship Awards are not restricted to one pregnancy and, therefore, pregnant academic staff who</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ha</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ve previously </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">received the award</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> may make additional applications when taking maternity leave again.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="23" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18.15pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">In October 2012, a survey was carried out of all staff members who took maternity leave in the previous 4 years. The response rate was very high, with 85% of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">eligible staff participating. The data provided was used to inform and develop College HR strategy in this area</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, and a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> ‘babies and bumps’ staff networking group has also been established to allow parents and expectant parents an opportunity to network and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">socialise.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18.15pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">What role should the government have in encouraging the retention of women in academic STEM careers?</span></p><ol start="24" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18.15pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18.15pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Th</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">e accessibility and affordability of good childcare is </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">of</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> concern to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">all </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">parents</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and may be a particular barrier to women in deciding to pur</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">sue and maintain an academic STEM career</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.  T</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">he College would welcome any action taken by the government to support and enhance provision in the form of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">any further </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">tax breaks for parents</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> or </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">other actions </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">or provisions </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">which would support effective</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and aff</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ordable</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> childcare</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, both during school hours and after-school</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18.15pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="25" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18.15pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18.15pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The College would suggest that the relevant government departments work with research councils </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">and other research funders </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">to</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> standardise</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> the rules regarding the treatment of pay and the ‘holdi</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ng’ of grants while researchers take periods of maternity leave. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Standardisation of treatment is also an important issue.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18.15pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="26" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18.15pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18.15pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Research Councils should ensure that consideration of gender issues is included on research funding application forms as is required </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">for EU grants</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="27" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18.15pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18.15pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The government </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">might</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> consider rewarding those HE institutions which are being active and creative in attempting to address this issue of national economic and cultural importance</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> so that they may continue to be innovative and committed</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Th</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ere has been considerable and sustained effort and significant resource allocated</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> for many, many years</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. The College has achieved some success but, it has not made real inroads</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> into</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, or stemmed</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> the ‘leaky pipeline’ challenge as evidence</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">d</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> by our representat</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ion figures.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="28" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18.15pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18.15pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Data should be collected on the destinations </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">and experiences </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">of those who have completed their PhDs</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">in order to identify if there are any factors that may be addressed by HE institutions</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> or the government</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="29" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18.15pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18.15pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The squeeze on the number of academ</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ic jobs </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">available in HE </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">obviously limits the number of opportunities available for which women, in particular, can apply. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> The same is true for the limited number of fellowships which are available.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">  The financial climate, in general, is not helpful for </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">promoting diversity and so actions to support well-managed and efficiently-run HE institutions should be considered as a key method of stimulating higher education’s contribution to the UK economy.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">September 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div><hr style="width:33%; height:1px; text-align:left" /><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn1"></a><a href="#_ftnref1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> Pledge to Academic Women, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">http://www3.imperial.ac.uk/equality/staf</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">fnetworksandcommittees/aoc/pledge</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn2"></a><a href="#_ftnref2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">The Medal and Awards</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">are</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">named in honour of</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">Professor Dame Julia Higgins</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">FRS, FREng, Professor of Polymer Science, now a S</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">enior Research Investigator in Chemical Engineering, and previously the first female Dean of the City and Guilds College and the first female Principal of the Faculty of Engineering</span></p></body></html>